info:
Labor Law Background or related experience is Preferred

As a Legal Intern in HSBC China's legal department, you will have a unique opportunity to work with a team of experienced in-house legal counsels who have expertise in a variety of practice areas including but not limited to wholesale/retail banking products and services, digital legal services, data privacy, competition law, employment law, regulatory compliance and litigation. 

You will have a broad range of responsibilities which may include (all under the supervision of the relevant in-house legal counsel):
1) Conducting legal research and preparing research paper on the legal issues/matters on requested topics; 
2) Translation of legal documents and materials; 
3) Assisting in the low-risk legal documentation drafting and review
4) Other legal assignment as needed from time to time. 

Requirement:
1) Pursuing a Master's Degree in Law (second year student is preferred) with outstanding academic performance, Bachelor Degree in Law is preferred; 
2) Fluent in both Chinese and English; 
3) Good legal thinking and legal drafting skills;
4) Ability to research and learn new legal issues quickly to facilitate problem solving

Responsibilities:

-	Assist in contract signing procedure, including obtaining signature/chop, scanning, couriering the contract documents and completing contract filling of daily business contracts of all legal entities in APAC;
-	Assist in maintaining Costar database of all legal entities in APAC under supervision (e.g. preparation on submittal/checklist, follow up on the signing progress and cross-check key dates);
-	Assist to provide personal identification documents/business licenses in accordance with company policy;
-	Assist in circulating board resolution for signature for AGM/ other matters across APAC;
-	Assist in legal research;
-	Contract filing and execution copy follow up
-	Review and proof reading on contracts that under company templates;
-	Translation of contract terms;
-	Coordinate for new vendor creation/payment of legal bills;
-	Other ad hoc work assigned by APAC Legal team;

Requirements:

-	University Student with major in Law
-	Details-oriented
-	Good command of English and Mandarin
-	Support at least 3 full days a week
